<p>
  If you're looking for a private app for two, <strong>Between</strong> is one of the first names you'll find — it's the veteran of the category, around since 2011. <strong>OurCouple</strong> is a newer, all-in-one private space built around daily rituals, memories and playful games. Here's the honest comparison.
</p>

<h2>The Short Version</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Between</strong> is a private messenger for two: chat, a shared photo &amp; video album, a calendar with anniversary countdowns, free voice calls, and a chronological memory timeline. It's free (ad-supported), with a one-time <strong>$26.99 lifetime</strong> upgrade.</li>
  <li><strong>OurCouple</strong> is an all-in-one private space: a daily message + photo of the day, daily questions, a shared memory journal, love notes, a calendar, couple games with a <strong>compatibility score</strong>, and a virtual pet you raise together — all end-to-end encrypted, with one subscription that covers both partners.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  <strong>Short answer:</strong> if you mainly want a private chat and a shared album with someone you message all day, Between is the proven pick. If you want a space built around daily rituals, memories and games — not just messaging — OurCouple is the better fit.
</p>

