<h2>Pricing</h2>

<p>
  Between is free with ads, and a one-time <strong>$26.99 lifetime</strong> purchase removes them and adds sticker packs. OurCouple is freemium — a generous free tier, and a single premium subscription unlocks everything for <em>both</em> of you, so you never pay twice. If a one-time price is what matters most, Between's lifetime deal is hard to beat. If you want everything in one private, ad-free space, OurCouple's shared plan is the better value.
</p>

<h2>Privacy</h2>

<p>
  OurCouple encrypts your shared content end-to-end. Between, like most ad-supported apps, does not advertise end-to-end encryption. If keeping your relationship data genuinely private matters to you — and it should — that's a real distinction. We explain why in <a href="/blog/relationship-data-encryption">why your relationship data deserves encryption</a>.
</p>

<h2>Who Each App Is For</h2>

<h3>Choose Between if…</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You want a dependable private messenger with a shared timeline</li>
  <li>Free voice calls matter to you</li>
  <li>You'd rather pay once (lifetime) than subscribe</li>
  <li>You don't need games, rituals, or a virtual pet</li>
</ul>

<h3>Choose OurCouple if…</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You want daily rituals — a message, a photo, a love note</li>
  <li>You want memories, plans and games in one private place</li>
  <li>You care about end-to-end encryption</li>
  <li>You want one subscription that covers both partners</li>
</ul>

